Django Backend

Django runs on Python, so it needs a Python virtual environment (venv).

This venv isolates your projectâ€™s Python packages (like Django, djangorestframework, etc.) from your global Python setup.

Example setup:

# Inside your backend folder
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate       # On Mac/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate          # On Windows

pip install django djangorestframework

