React runs on Node.js, not Python.

It uses npm or yarn to manage dependencies.

So, you donâ€™t use venv here â€” instead, you use node_modules created by npm.

Example setup:

# Inside your frontend folder
npm create vite@latest frontend -- --template react
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev


This automatically sets up Reactâ€™s environment using Node.

