ğŸ§© Option 1:
sudo apt install python3-django


â†’ Installs Django system-wide (for all users).

âš ï¸ Not Recommended for Projects

Because:

It installs Django globally, not in your projectâ€™s virtual environment.

You canâ€™t easily control or upgrade its version per project.

It may cause version conflicts if you have multiple Django projects.

Use this only if you want a quick test or to run a global Django setup (not for development).

ğŸ§  Option 2:
pip install django djangorestframework


â†’ Installs Django inside your virtual environment (venv).

âœ… Recommended for Development

Because:

Keeps your project isolated (no global mess).

You can easily manage versions in your requirements.txt.

Works well when deploying or sharing your code.

Typical setup:

# create and activate venv
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate     # Linux/macOS
venv\Scripts\activate        # Windows

# then install Django and DRF
pip install django djangorestframework

ğŸ’¡ Summary
Command	Installs Where	Recommended?	Use Case
